---
import '../styles/global.css';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>License — Cloud Sovereignty Index</title>
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-900 min-h-screen">
  <header class="border-b border-gray-200 px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
    <a href="/" class="font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight">Cloud Sovereignty Index</a>
    <nav class="flex gap-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <a href="/faq" class="hover:text-gray-900">FAQ</a>
      <a href="/methodology" class="hover:text-gray-900">Methodology</a>
      <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-gray-900">Privacy</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/mattpltn/cloud-sovereignty-index" class="hover:text-gray-900" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 prose prose-gray">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">License</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)</p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      The Cloud Sovereignty Index — including its source code, scoring methodology, criteria mappings, and documentation — is licensed under the
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 underline">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">You are free to</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li><strong>Share</strong> — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format</li>
      <li><strong>Adapt</strong> — remix, transform, and build upon the material</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Under the following terms</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li>
        <strong>Attribution</strong> — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license,
        and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but not in any way
        that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>NonCommercial</strong> — You may not use the material for commercial purposes.
        This includes selling assessments, integrating into paid products or services, or using
        this tool as part of a consulting or audit offering without permission.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">No additional restrictions</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      You may not apply legal terms or technological measures that legally restrict others from doing
      anything the license permits.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Commercial use</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      If you are interested in commercial use — for example, integrating this framework into a paid
      compliance product, offering it as part of a consulting service, or white-labelling the tool —
      please open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/mattpltn/cloud-sovereignty-index" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 underline">GitHub</a> to discuss.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Third-party content</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The criteria in this tool are derived from the BSI C5:2020 catalogue and the EU Cloud Sovereignty
      Framework v1.2.1. These documents are published by their respective authors under their own terms.
      This tool is not affiliated with or endorsed by BSI or the European Commission.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-600">
      Full license text: <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 underline">creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode</a>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-gray-100 px-6 py-6 text-center text-xs text-gray-400 mt-12">
    Cloud Sovereignty Index v1.0 ·
    <a href="/methodology" class="underline">Methodology</a> ·
    <a href="/privacy" class="underline">Privacy</a> ·
    <a href="https://github.com/mattpltn/cloud-sovereignty-index" class="underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
